Sean Garrett sends:

> My tranny is out too (also the axels) and I want to bolt them both up
> together then mount them both back into the van as one unit. Can I do this
> or will I run into some weird axel problem (not being able to put them in
> unless I mount the tranny 1st) ????

The official procedure on a Loaf is to bolt the transmission and engine
together then raise them as a unit. It should work on Vanagons too.

Hang the engine/transmission pack then mount the stub axles.
